ese are the first\ndedicated limits on $L_{\\mu}$ $-$ $L_{\\tau}$ models at the LHC and result in a\nsignificant increase in the excluded model parameter space. The results of this\nsearch may also be used to constrain the coupling strength of any light Z$'$\ngauge boson to muons.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 10 Aug 2018 19:26:16 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 11 Apr 2019 12:54:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-04-12"}
